                <head>No. 441.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Andrews</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation or the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 10, 1872</date>. (Received May
                        29.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 158]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I take pleasure in being able to inform you that
                    during the past three months there has been in Sweden an almost general increase
                    of the wages of mechanics 25 per cent.</p>
                <p>This is owing, aside from the prevailing prosperity, partly to the organizations
                    which workingmen have effected and partly to the influence of emigration, which
                    is going on with marked activity. It is considered by those who have
                    investigated the matter that the cost of living here has increased 50 per cent,
                    in the past fifteen or twenty years.</p>
                <p>I have. &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C. C. ANDREWS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
